c basics
header file:
 file with extension . h
 <> shld be used(it search in current wrking directory)
 " " used menas it search in directory if not found thn in file
 which contains C function declarations and macro definitions shared between several source files.
 two types:
 -the files that the programmer writes
 -the files that comes with your compiler
preprocessor directives:
 built-in predefined function or macro
 that acts as a directive to the compiler
 it gets executed before the actual C Program is executed.
